<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup/M1: light pickup note A4; ⑥ Bm LH B2-F#3-B3, ⑤ A A2-E3-A3
- M2-3: oscillating ①/④ and ①/⑤ — RH 2-note open thirds
- M4: ①¹ first inversion for variety on repeated D
- M5: high RH D5-F#5 (open 10th) — brief moment of spaciousness
- M6: ⑤ A full — 3-note RH A4-C#5-E5 as A "rises" melodically
- M7-8: high melody D5 — RH doubles it F#5-D5, creating shining quality
- M9: ②7 Em7 full bass E2-B2-D3-G3 — emotional depth
- M11: ④ G full 4-note G2-D3-G3-B3 with sustained RH layer
- M14: ⑤² second inversion E2-A2-E3-A3 — suspension before final
- M15: ⑦° C#° passing — chromatic bass motion C#2→D2
- M16: ① "334" D full close, D1 pedal — serene resolution

VOICE LEADING:
- M8→9: D5 common in RH across ①→⑥
- M12: ②→④ bass steps E→G — smooth inner line
- M14: A2 (pedal ⑤) connects back to D2 (①) across measures
- LH pedal tracks chord root D1 through pickup and final

TEXTURE ARC:
- Light 3/4 opening — pickup feel, simple 2-note RH
- M5-8: Upward motion of melody to D5 — RH follows up
- M9-12: Middle emotional section — Em7 depth, Em full bass
- M13-15: Return with ⑤² suspension (M14) and ⑦° passing (M15)
- M16: Quiet ① final — intimate 3/4 close, no fanfare
-->
